          To shut down an nnnnmmmmbbbbdddd process it is recommended that SIGKILL
          (-9) NNNNOOOOTTTT be used, except as a last resort, as this may leave
          the name database in an inconsistent state.  The correct way
          to terminate nnnnmmmmbbbbdddd is to send it a SIGTERM (-15) signal and
          wait for it to die on its own.

          nnnnmmmmbbbbdddd will accept SIGHUP, which will cause it to dump out its
          namelists into the file _n_a_m_e_l_i_s_t._d_e_b_u_g in the
          /_u_s_r/_l_o_c_a_l/_s_a_m_b_a/_v_a_r/_l_o_c_k_s directory (or the _v_a_r/_l_o_c_k_s
